NAME
	topic_lookup - discover the list of existing topics

SYNOPSIS
	#include <topic.h>

	int topic_lookup(topicid_t topic_ids[], size_t count)

DESCRIPTION
	topic_lookup() allows a process to discover what topics there are. The list of existing topic IDs is returned in the provided array 'topic_ids' of size 'count'.
	The user must provide a large enough array otherwise ERANGE is raised.

RETURN VALUE
	On success, the number of existing topics is returned and topic_ids contains the topic IDs. Otherwise, a value of -1 is returned, and the global variable errno is set to indicate the error.

ERRORS
	If the provided array is too small, ERANGE is returned.
	If any other error occurs, EGENERIC is returned.
